@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "FAQ";
}

<div class="content-section">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>How do I borrow a book?</h4>
        <p>Navigate to the "Borrow Book" page, select an available book from the dropdown list, enter your name and email, then click "Borrow Book". The system will automatically set a due date 14 days from the borrowing date.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>How long can I keep a borrowed book?</h4>
        <p>Books can be borrowed for 14 days from the date of borrowing. The due date is automatically calculated and displayed in your borrowing record.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>How do I return a book?</h4>
        <p>Go to the "View Report" page and find your borrowing record. Click the "Return" button next to your record. The system will mark the book as returned and make it available for others.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>What information is needed to add a new book?</h4>
        <p>You need to provide the book's title, author, ISBN, category (optional), section, and rack ID. This information helps organize books and makes them easy to locate in the library.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>How do I find a specific book in the library?</h4>
        <p>Check the "View Report" page which lists all books with their section and rack ID locations. You can use this information to physically locate the book in the library.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>Can I borrow a book that's currently borrowed by someone else?</h4>
        <p>No, only available books appear in the borrowing dropdown list. Once a book is returned, it becomes available again for borrowing.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>What are sections and rack IDs?</h4>
        <p>Sections are major categories in the library (Fiction, Non-Fiction, Reference). Rack IDs are specific location codes (like A1, B5) that indicate exactly where a book is shelved.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h4>How can I view all my borrowing history?</h4>
        <p>Visit the "View Report" page where all borrowing records are displayed, including borrow dates, due dates, and return status.</p>
    </div>
</div>